\p 
\v 36 At that time my sanity returned to me. I was restored to the honor of my kingdom, and my splendor returned to me. My ministers and my nobles were seeking me out, and I was reinstated over my kingdom. I became even greater than before.
\v 37 Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and exalt and glorify the King of heaven, for all his deeds are right and his ways are just. He is able to bring down those who live in pride.
\c 5
\p 
\v 1 \w King|strong="H4430"\w* \w Belshazzar|strong="H1113"\w* \w prepared|strong="H5648"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w great|strong="H7229"\w* \w banquet|strong="H3900"\w* \w for|strong="H6903"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* thousand \w of|strong="H4430"\w* his \w nobles|strong="H7261"\w*, \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w he|strong="H6903"\w* \w was|strong="H4430"\w* \w drinking|strong="H8355"\w* \w wine|strong="H2562"\w* \w in|strong="H4430"\w* \w front|strong="H6903"\w* \w of|strong="H4430"\w* them all.
