\v 25 “\w This|strong="H1836"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H1768"\w* \w writing|strong="H3792"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H3792"\w* inscribed: \sc \w MENE|strong="H4484"\w*\sc*, \sc \w MENE|strong="H4484"\w*\sc*, \sc \w TEQEL|strong="H8625"\w*\sc*, \w and|strong="H3792"\w* \sc \w PHARSIN|strong="H6537"\w*\sc*.
\v 26 \w This|strong="H1836"\w* \w is|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H1836"\w* \w interpretation|strong="H6591"\w* \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H1836"\w* \w words|strong="H4406"\w*: \w As|strong="H4437"\w* for \it mene\it* – God \w has|strong="H4437"\w* \w numbered|strong="H4483"\w* \w your|strong="H4483"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w*’s days \w and|strong="H4437"\w* brought it \w to|strong="H4483"\w* \w an|strong="H4437"\w* \w end|strong="H8000"\w*.
\v 27 \it As for teqel\it* – you are \w weighed|strong="H8625"\w* on the \w balances|strong="H3977"\w* \w and|strong="H3977"\w* \w found|strong="H7912"\w* to be lacking.
\v 28 \w As|strong="H4437"\w* for \it peres\it* – \w your|strong="H3052"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w* \w is|strong="H4437"\w* \w divided|strong="H6537"\w* \w and|strong="H4076"\w* \w given|strong="H3052"\w* over \w to|strong="H3052"\w* \w the|strong="H3052"\w* \w Medes|strong="H4076"\w* \w and|strong="H4076"\w* \w Persians|strong="H6540"\w*.”
\p 
\v 29 \w Then|strong="H1768"\w*, \w on|strong="H5922"\w* \w Belshazzar|strong="H1113"\w*’s orders, \w Daniel|strong="H1841"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* \w clothed|strong="H3848"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* purple, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w golden|strong="H1722"\w* \w collar|strong="H2002"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* placed \w around|strong="H5922"\w* \w his|strong="H5922"\w* \w neck|strong="H6676"\w*, \w and|strong="H1722"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* \w proclaimed|strong="H3745"\w* \w third|strong="H8531"\w* \w ruler|strong="H7990"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H5922"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w*.
\v 30 \w And|strong="H4430"\w* \w in|strong="H4430"\w* \w that|strong="H4430"\w* very \w night|strong="H3916"\w* \w Belshazzar|strong="H1113"\w*, \w the|strong="H4430"\w* Babylonian \w king|strong="H4430"\w*, \w was|strong="H4430"\w* \w killed|strong="H6992"\w*.
\v 31 So Darius the Mede took control of the kingdom when he was about sixty-two years old.
\c 6
\p 
\v 1 It seemed like \w a|strong="H3068"\w* good idea \w to|strong="H1868"\w* \w Darius|strong="H1868"\w* \w to|strong="H1868"\w* appoint over \w the|strong="H1868"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w* 120 satraps who would be \w in|strong="H4437"\w* charge \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w the|strong="H1868"\w* entire \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w*.
\v 2 \w Over|strong="H5922"\w* \w them|strong="H5922"\w* \w would|strong="H1934"\w* \w be|strong="H1934"\w* three supervisors, one \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w whom|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* Daniel. These satraps \w were|strong="H1934"\w* accountable \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w them|strong="H5922"\w*, \w so|strong="H1768"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* king’s interests \w might|strong="H1934"\w* not \w incur|strong="H1934"\w* damage.
\v 3 \w Now|strong="H4430"\w* \w this|strong="H4481"\w* \w Daniel|strong="H1841"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* distinguishing himself above \w the|strong="H4481"\w* other \w supervisors|strong="H5632"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* satraps, \w for|strong="H1768"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w had|strong="H4430"\w* \w an|strong="H4430"\w* extraordinary spirit. \w In|strong="H4430"\w* fact, \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* intended \w to|strong="H4481"\w* appoint \w him|strong="H4481"\w* \w over|strong="H5924"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* entire kingdom.
\v 4 Consequently \w the|strong="H3606"\w* \w supervisors|strong="H5632"\w* \w and|strong="H4430"\w* satraps \w were|strong="H1934"\w* trying \w to|strong="H5922"\w* find some pretext \w against|strong="H5922"\w* \w Daniel|strong="H1841"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* connection \w with|strong="H1841"\w* administrative matters. \w But|strong="H3606"\w* \w they|strong="H3606"\w* \w were|strong="H1934"\w* unable \w to|strong="H5922"\w* find \w any|strong="H3606"\w* \w such|strong="H1836"\w* damaging evidence, \w because|strong="H6903"\w* \w he|strong="H1768"\w* \w was|strong="H1934"\w* trustworthy \w and|strong="H4430"\w* guilty \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w no|strong="H3606"\w* negligence \w or|strong="H4430"\w* corruption.
\v 5 \w So|strong="H1768"\w* these \w men|strong="H4437"\w* concluded, “\w We|strong="H1768"\w* won’t \w find|strong="H7912"\w* \w any|strong="H3606"\w* \w pretext|strong="H5931"\w* \w against|strong="H5922"\w* \w this|strong="H1932"\w* man \w Daniel|strong="H1841"\w* unless \w it|strong="H1934"\w* \w is|strong="H1768"\w* \w in|strong="H5922"\w* connection \w with|strong="H1841"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* law \w of|strong="H4437"\w* \w his|strong="H5922"\w* God.”
\p 
\v 6 \w So|strong="H1768"\w* \w these|strong="H1836"\w* supervisors \w and|strong="H1841"\w* satraps \w came|strong="H1768"\w* by collusion \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* king \w and|strong="H1841"\w* said \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w him|strong="H5922"\w*, “\w O|strong="H3068"\w* King Darius, live forever!
